                    <span>I found the book not usefull at all.  Simple things on how to write a loop is so full of text without addressing the simple issue of how to write a simple while loop with a counter.  I found the examples sparse and irrelevant to what i was doing.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A great book about Korn shell programming</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>7</span>
                      /
                      <span>8</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-12-03</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I gave it 5 stars partially because it was given just 1 star unjustly by a few reviewers. From a number of complaining reviews, one realizes that the book title is little misleading. It's not a book for a true beginner wanting to read about "simple" examples of shell programs and looking for detailed explanations line by line. This book is concise, to the point, and really explains "Korn" shell's features. Even as early as chapter 4 about Korn shell basics, things are explained that a long-time shell programmers may not know. If you do and have done serious, real world Korn shell programming, you'll appreciate it.<p>There were also complains about hard to find things in the book. But from my experience, it's not the case if one really reads it from cover to cover and unerstands the topics presented chapter by chapter. I agree that the book may not be a great reference book, but it was not written as one.</span>
                  
              
